cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.CV, cs.MA 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category as it discusses the use of reinforcement learning for achieving human-level performance in a complex multiplayer game. The paper also involves the use of a population-based approach for training the agents, which falls under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of game points scored as input suggests the involvement of game theory, which falls under the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. The use of pixels as input suggests the involvement of computer vision, which falls under the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the use of multiple agents learning and acting independently suggests the involvement of multi-agent systems, which falls under the cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) sub-category.
